                        <objectDesc form="codex">
                            <supportDesc material="perg">
                                <support>
                                    <p>
                                        <material> Parchment; the last three quires as well as the
                                            flyleaf are of a lighter parchment than the rest of the
                                            manuscript. </material>
                                    </p>
                                </support>
                                <extent>i + 248 (inkl. 126<hi rend="sup">bis</hi>). The flyleaf in
                                    front is foliated as leaf <locus>1</locus> and ff. <locus from="237r" to="238r">237r-238r</locus> were originally
                                    blank; the following leaves are blank. <dimensions type="leaf" scope="all">
                                        <height>142</height>
                                        <width>100</width>
                                    </dimensions>. </extent>
                                <foliation>
                                    <p>The manuscript is foliated 1-147 in black ink. The foliation
                                        includes the front flyleaf and the blank leaves in the back
                                        of the manuscript. </p>
                                </foliation>
