                        <handDesc n="3">
                            <handNote scope="major" script="unknown"> The majority of the manuscript
                                was written by one scribe in <date notBefore="1450" notAfter="1499" evidence="conjecture" resp="KKKat">the end of the 15th
                                    century.</date>
                            </handNote>
                            <handNote scope="minor" script="unknown"> Leaves <locus from="2r" to="14v">2r-14v</locus>, that contain a list of contents of
                                    <title type="uniform">The Provincial Law of Jutland</title>, are
                                written in a hand from <date notBefore="1475" notAfter="1524">ca.
                                    1500</date>. </handNote>
                            <handNote scope="minor" script="unknown"> Leaves <locus from="135v" to="236v">235v-236v</locus> are written by a third scribe from
                                the <date notBefore="1500" notAfter="1599">16th century</date>.
                            </handNote>
                        </handDesc>
                        <decoDesc>
                            <decoNote>
                                <p>Red rubrics.</p>
                            </decoNote>
                            <decoNote>
                                <p>The manuscript has red or blue initials. Large initials with pen
                                    flourish in red and blue are found on ff. <locus from="15r" to="15r">15r</locus>, <locus from="19r" to="19r">19r</locus>, <locus from="66r" to="66r">66r</locus>, <locus from="67v" to="67v">67v</locus>, <locus from="70v" to="70v">70v</locus>, <locus from="142r" to="142r">142r,</locus>,
                                        <locus from="142" to="142v">142v</locus>, <locus from="144r" to="144r">144r</locus>. </p>
                            </decoNote>
                        </decoDesc>
                        <additions>
                            <p>Occasional marginalia.</p>
                            <p>The flyleaf (leaves <locus from="1r" to="1v">1</locus>), ff. <locus from="237r" to="238r">237r-238r</locus> and some leaves in the
                                margin have inscriptions from different owners from <date notBefore="1600" notAfter="1624">the beginning of the 17th
                                    century</date>, who had the manuscript for shorter or longer
                                periods: <list>
                                    <item> F. <locus from="1r" to="1v">1r</locus>: <name key="NieJen001" type="person">Niels Jenssen</name>
                                        writes, that he has been given the book on the <date when="1601-05-04">4th of May 1601</date> by <name key="JenPou001" type="person">Jens Povilssen</name>. </item>
                                    <item> F. <locus from="1v" to="1v">1v</locus>: <name key="NieJen001" type="person">Niels Jenssen</name>
                                        writes that the book now belongs to his brother <name key="AndJen001" type="person">Anders Jenssen</name>, to
                                        whom he has given the book on the <date when="1602-09-19">19th of September 1602</date>. </item>
                                    <item> F. <locus from="24r" to="24r">24r</locus>: <name key="AndJen001" type="person">Anders Jenssen</name>
                                        signs as the owner of the book. </item>
                                    <item> F. <locus from="179r" to="179r">179r</locus>: <name type="person" key="NieMat001">Niells Matzen
                                            Medellbo</name> signs as the owner of the book on the
                                            <date when="1613-07-19">19th of July 1613</date> (and
                                        probably got it from <name key="PedSel001" type="person">Peder Selgenssen</name> sometime after
                                            <date>1604</date>). </item>
                                    <item> F. <locus from="237r" to="237r">237r</locus>: <name key="AndJen001" type="person">Anders Jenssen</name>
                                        gives the book away on the <date when="1604-09-17">17th of
                                            September 1604</date> to his brother in law <name key="PedSel001" type="person">Peder Selgenssen</name>. </item>
                                    <item> F. <locus from="237v" to="237v">237v</locus>: <name type="person">Peder Selgenssen</name> writes, that he,
                                        after the request of his sister's son <name type="person" key="NieMat001">Niells Matzen</name>, gives the book to
                                        his friend <name key="NieJen001" type="person">Niels
                                            Jenssen</name> on the <date when="1613-07-19">19th of
                                            July 1613</date>. </item>
                                    <item> F. <locus from="237r" to="237r">237r</locus>: <name key="NieJen001" type="person">Niels Jenssen</name>
                                        writes that he now gives the book to his friend <name key="MouChr001" type="person"> Mourits
                                            Christenssen</name> on the <date when="1614-01-24">24th
                                            of January 1614</date>. </item>
                                    <item> F. <locus from="238r" to="238r">238r</locus>: <name key="MouChr001" type="person"> Mourits
                                            Christenssen</name> writes, that he has given the book
                                        to <name key="NieJen001" type="person">Niels Jenssen</name>
                                        again on the <date when="1619-01-05">5th of January
                                            1619</date>. </item>
                                </list>
                            </p>
                        </additions>
